Siasitok Sign Language AR Card is a new teaching aids to learn sign language, thus AR Flashcards make learning fun with the technology of Augmented Reality. This flashcard provided with Augmented Reality (AR) technology. By having this technology, ones can learn sign language at anytime, anywhere, easy, cheap, faster and effective.
Deaf person in Malaysia only around 66,000 out of 30 million people in Malaysia making there are minority people in their own country. They are looking like normal people but they are lacking their sense of hearing organ. This might be the problem for them because they canâ€°Ã›Âªt to use the public facility like us, normal person. Not that all, family problem also the cause for deaf people. In normal family, possibility to get deaf child is possible. So parents will try to ask the child to use hearing aids or put implant to the child. This can increase the cost because the hearing aids is costly RM2000 to RM 18,000 and the implant costly around RM50,000 with government subsidies and RM150,000 without subsidies. The problem is, are the deaf have enough money to do the implant? This is the big problem for them. This is also the cause deaf person feels marginalized from normal person. They canâ€°Ã›Âªt speak or communicate to normal person normally and feeling isolated when they try to say something to normal person.

So we came out with the solution teaching aids â€°Ã›Ã’ Siasitok Sign Language AR Flashcard to learn sign language more easy, cheap, faster and efficient.

Motivated by her personal experience of growing up with a significant birthmark on her face, Rozella Mahjhrin turned her struggles with bullying and mental health issues into a social awareness platform called True Complexion. Created in 2015, True Complexion uses narrative and photography to tell stories of individuals living with differences related to disabilities, medical conditions, mental health issues and body image issues. Since then, the platform has expanded into an inclusive event called Alive! Festival, and a podcast series (which will be launched later this year). This passion project has been run with zero budget, and Rozella's intention is to transform it into a financially sustainable social enterprise that will continue creating impact in the community. The goal of True Complexion is to humanise the various conditions that people live with. change societal's perceptionÃ¥ÃŠof the differently-abled community, empower individuals from the community who are often unseen and unheard, plus create a more diverse and inclusive Malaysia.

Urban Farm Tech is an urban farm solution system provider which designs and builds urban farming systems. Urban Farm Tech also provides coaching and education relating to urban farms. 
The current food system has an overreliance on imports worth RM52 billion in the year 2018, where food travels a long distance before arriving to our homes. A self sustaining food system within the country itself is essential to preserve a high level of food security.
Urban Farm Tech aims to inspire young farmers from urban and rural regions to adopt modern agriculture technology to support the growth of our future national food systems. In order to achieve this vision, Urban Farm Tech is actively involved in Urban Farm Projects with schools & community. Through the projects in schools & community, we bring new farming ideas & technology such as vertical farming, IoT smart farm and Aquaponics to the young generation. Urban Farm Tech also provides training to these students and community on modern farming technology and help them learn new survival skills through urban farming.

startup_name: Komuniti Tukang Jahit - by KTJ Culture Venture
startup_oneliner: KTJ empowers underprivileged women by providing sewing orders of premium corporate gifts, through the training provided by KTJ. Enabling them to earn a side income from the comfort of their own home.
startup_desc:
KTJ is a community consisting of  single ladies, single moms, stay-at-home moms and under privileged women. KTJ aims to empower them with sewing skills & providing them sewing orders to allow them to earn an income through sewing.

After the experience of working with home-based tailors for about 2 years, we noticed that there is an issue that has yet to be solved. Women in the targeted group are unable to commit to a full-time employment because they are fully committed to taking care of the home and the children. However, some of them already possess the sewing skills & even own their own sewing machines. 

KTJ is established to provide guidance, sewing skills and knowledge and by linking sewing orders to the targeted group - so that they would be able to work flexibly and commit to orders that they are capable of - while working from home and taking care of their children

KTJ is targeting to help the community in-need because, we believe in giving back to the community by creating jobs and offering a steady source of income.

startup_oneliner: Me.reka is an open-source education platform that advocates for learning outside the traditional classroom paired with unconventional fun!
startup_desc:
Me.reka is an open-source education platform that advocates for learning outside the traditional classroom paired with unconventional fun! At Me.reka, anyone can come together to share ideas, pick up new skills, and make things.
Me.reka is an innovative and alternative education space. By removing all barriers to designing and making, we teach students and professionals to excel in the industries and businesses that will shape the future of Malaysia.

Me.reka provides access to tools, technology and experts. Using highly collaborative and immersive methods, we sharpen the skills that students and professionals need to flourish in our rapidly changing world. All of us must learn to adapt to evolving industries; all of us must play our part in solving complex and global problems.

The ecosystem at Me.reka brings together students, professionals, communities and makers, and connects them to real projects and income-generating opportunities. Together, we build sustainable solutions and realise our potential.
